Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{400%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with 
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Cook on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, add @water{100%ml} (double for 4p) to a large #pot{} over high heat.

Add the @BBQ sauce{2%sachet}, @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}, @chipotle paste{1%sachet} and a 
pinch of salt and pepper.

Bring the sauce to the boil, giving it a good stir to ensure everything is combined.

Once the sauce is boiling lower heat to medium, add the @Irish chicken breast{260%grams}(diced) and 
cover with a #lid{}.

Simmer until chicken is cooked and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Stir halfway through and 
lower heat if necessary.

Once cooked, remove pot from heat and transfer just the chicken to a #board{} with a 
#slotted spoon{}.

Roughly chop the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is 
> safe to eat when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Trim and coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated) (no need to peel).

Drain and rinse @black beans{1/2%pack} in a #sieve{}. Pop half the beans (double for 4p) 
into a #medium bowl{} and roughly mash with a #fork{}.

Once the chicken is cooked and out of the pot, add the beans from the bowl and carrot to 
the remaining sauce in the pot.

Stir everything together, then boil until reduced to a thick sauce, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir back in the chicken and simmer for ~{2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Stir frequently and cook for a bit longer if you need to. You want it really thick!

When the wedges are ready, transfer them to an #ovenproof dish{}.

Spoon the chicken mixture on top of the wedges.

Sprinkle on the @grated cheese{50%grams} and bake in the oven until the cheese is golden 
and bubbly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Remove from the oven, sprinkle over the scallion and serve.